summary: This is an email chain from June 2021 between a US Attorney's Office contractor and an FBI Special Agent regarding the transfer of over 200GB of data for the Ghislaine Maxwell case via the USAfx file sharing system. The emails discuss logistical coordination for uploading the large dataset.

events.title: Initial request for USAfx coordination
events.description: A request is made for a US Attorney's Office contractor to coordinate with an FBI Special Agent to receive a new file for the Maxwell case via USAfx.

events.title: Data upload coordination
events.description: The FBI Special Agent requests the location of the USAfx folder to begin uploading over 200GB of Maxwell case data, and the contractor provides the link and logistical advice.

keyFacts: Over 200GB of data related to the Ghislaine Maxwell case was being transferred from the FBI to the US Attorney's Office in June 2021.
The data transfer was coordinated via the USAfx (US Attorney's Office File Exchange) system, with logistical advice to split large uploads.
The FBI agent involved was from the New York Office's Child Exploitation and Human Trafficking Task Force.
The email chain shows ongoing investigative activity and evidence handling in the Maxwell case over a year after her arrest.
Multiple individuals are referenced but their names are redacted in the document, indicated by placeholders like (USANYS) [Contractor].
